The intact luminal NPC1-C consists of residues 372 to 640. In our crystal structure, only residues 384 to 624 are visible (Figure S2
). We cannot see the electron density for the N-terminal 12 amino acids and C-terminal 16 amino acids (Figure S2), indicating that these regions might be flexible loops. It is assumed that, with these flexible N-terminal and C-terminal loops, the domain C can protrude from the endosomal membrane (Figure S3
) and be easily bound by the primed GP molecule.
